        <Parent_String>Clupeidae (family) [300310608], Clupeiformes (order) [300310607], Actinopterygii (subclass) [300310217], Osteichthyes (class) [300265954], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing 15 species of small, oily, small-headed, streamlined, variously colored fish, some with silvery iridescent sides and metallic deep-blue backs, living in shallow temperate waters of the North Atlantic, the North Pacific, the Baltic Sea, and the Mediterranean Sea.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
